{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":896,"text":"Here's an intriguing fact."},{"time":3240,"text":"In the developed world,"},{"time":5040,"text":"everywhere, women live an average\nof six to eight years longer than men do."},{"time":10840,"text":"Six to eight years longer."},{"time":13160,"text":"That's, like, a huge gap."},{"time":16600,"text":"In 2015, the \"Lancet\" published an article"},{"time":19720,"text":"showing that men in rich countries"},{"time":22200,"text":"are twice as likely to die as women are"},{"time":25200,"text":"at any age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27080,"text":"But there is one place in the world"},{"time":30000,"text":"where men live as long as women."},{"time":32479,"text":"It's a remote, mountainous zone,"},{"time":34560,"text":"a blue zone,"},{"time":35800,"text":"where super longevity"},{"time":37320,"text":"is common to both sexes."},{"time":40040,"text":"This is the blue zone in Sardinia,"},{"time":41880,"text":"an Italian island in the Mediterranean,"},{"time":43920,"text":"between Corsica and Tunisia,"},{"time":46560,"text":"where there are six times\nas many centenarians"},{"time":49960,"text":"as on the Italian mainland,"},{"time":51880,"text":"less than 200 miles away."},{"time":53920,"text":"There are 10 times as many centenarians"},{"time":55840,"text":"as there are in North America."},{"time":58040,"text":"It's the only place\nwhere men live as long as women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61160,"text":"But why?"},{"time":62480,"text":"My curiosity was piqued."},{"time":64720,"text":"I decided to research the science\nand the habits of the place,"},{"time":68080,"text":"and I started with the genetic profile."},{"time":70520,"text":"I discovered soon enough"},{"time":72600,"text":"that genes account for just\n25 percent of their longevity."},{"time":76640,"text":"The other 75 percent is lifestyle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80200,"text":"So what does it take\nto live to 100 or beyond?"},{"time":83520,"text":"What are they doing right?"},{"time":85400,"text":"What you're looking at\nis an aerial view of Villagrande."},{"time":88680,"text":"It's a village at the epicenter\nof the blue zone"},{"time":91240,"text":"where I went to investigate this,"},{"time":93400,"text":"and as you can see, architectural beauty\nis not its main virtue,"},{"time":98840,"text":"density is:"},{"time":100480,"text":"tightly spaced houses,"},{"time":102480,"text":"interwoven alleys and streets."},{"time":105040,"text":"It means that the villagers' lives\nconstantly intersect."},{"time":109280,"text":"And as I walked through the village,"},{"time":111040,"text":"I could feel hundreds\nof pairs of eyes watching me"},{"time":114200,"text":"from behind doorways and curtains,"},{"time":116840,"text":"from behind shutters."},{"time":118600,"text":"Because like all ancient villages,"},{"time":121040,"text":"Villagrande couldn't have survived"},{"time":123640,"text":"without this structure,\nwithout its walls, without its cathedral,"},{"time":126920,"text":"without its village square,"},{"time":128840,"text":"because defense and social cohesion\ndefined its design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133920,"text":"Urban priorities changed as we moved\ntowards the industrial revolution"},{"time":137920,"text":"because infectious disease\nbecame the risk of the day."},{"time":140800,"text":"But what about now?"},{"time":142560,"text":"Now, social isolation\nis the public health risk of our time."},{"time":147960,"text":"Now, a third of the population says"},{"time":150480,"text":"they have two or fewer people to lean on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153960,"text":"But let's go to Villagrande\nnow as a contrast"},{"time":156760,"text":"to meet some centenarians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158840,"text":"Meet Giuseppe Murinu.\nHe's 102, a supercentenarian"},{"time":162760,"text":"and a lifelong resident\nof the village of Villagrande."},{"time":165840,"text":"He was a gregarious man."},{"time":167800,"text":"He loved to recount stories"},{"time":170120,"text":"such as how he lived like a bird"},{"time":171800,"text":"from what he could find\non the forest floor"},{"time":174120,"text":"during not one but two world wars,"},{"time":177520,"text":"how he and his wife,\nwho also lived past 100,"},{"time":180640,"text":"raised six children\nin a small, homey kitchen"},{"time":184000,"text":"where I interviewed him."},{"time":185960,"text":"Here he is with his sons\nAngelo and Domenico,"},{"time":188600,"text":"both in their 70s\nand looking after their father,"},{"time":191680,"text":"and who were quite frankly\nvery suspicious of me and my daughter"},{"time":195960,"text":"who came along with me\non this research trip,"},{"time":198720,"text":"because the flip side of social cohesion"},{"time":201560,"text":"is a wariness of strangers and outsiders."},{"time":204400,"text":"But Giuseppe, he wasn't suspicious at all."},{"time":208320,"text":"He was a happy-go-lucky guy,"},{"time":210280,"text":"very outgoing with a positive outlook."},{"time":213960,"text":"And I wondered: so is that what it takes\nto live to be 100 or beyond,"},{"time":218520,"text":"thinking positively?"},{"time":222000,"text":"Actually, no."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":228840,"text":"Meet Giovanni Corrias. He's 101,"},{"time":231480,"text":"the grumpiest person I have ever met."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":236040,"text":"And he put a lie to the notion"},{"time":237760,"text":"that you have to be positive\nto live a long life."},{"time":241400,"text":"And there is evidence for this."},{"time":243160,"text":"When I asked him why he lived so long,"},{"time":245720,"text":"he kind of looked at me\nunder hooded eyelids and he growled,"},{"time":249160,"text":"\"Nobody has to know my secrets.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":251320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":253560,"text":"But despite being a sourpuss,"},{"time":255800,"text":"the niece who lived with him\nand looked after him"},{"time":258160,"text":"called him \"Il Tesoro,\" \"my treasure.\""},{"time":261360,"text":"And she respected him and loved him,"},{"time":264560,"text":"and she told me, when I questioned\nthis obvious loss of her freedom,"},{"time":269400,"text":"\"You just don't understand, do you?"},{"time":271280,"text":"Looking after this man is a pleasure."},{"time":274000,"text":"It's a huge privilege for me."},{"time":276000,"text":"This is my heritage.\""},{"time":278040,"text":"And indeed, wherever I went\nto interview these centenarians,"},{"time":281720,"text":"I found a kitchen party."},{"time":283461,"text":"Here's Giovanni with his two nieces,"},{"time":285200,"text":"Maria above him"},{"time":286440,"text":"and beside him his great-niece Sara,"},{"time":288400,"text":"who came when I was there\nto bring fresh fruits and vegetables."},{"time":292200,"text":"And I quickly discovered by being there"},{"time":295520,"text":"that in the blue zone, as people age,"},{"time":297800,"text":"and indeed across their lifespans,"},{"time":300280,"text":"they're always surrounded\nby extended family, by friends,"},{"time":304400,"text":"by neighbors, the priest,\nthe barkeeper, the grocer."},{"time":307720,"text":"People are always there or dropping by."},{"time":310040,"text":"They are never left\nto live solitary lives."},{"time":313760,"text":"This is unlike the rest\nof the developed world,"},{"time":316320,"text":"where as George Burns quipped,"},{"time":317800,"text":"\"Happiness is having a large,\nloving, caring family in another city.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":322280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":324000,"text":"Now, so far we've only met men,"},{"time":327440,"text":"long-living men, but I met women too,"},{"time":329560,"text":"and here you see Zia Teresa."},{"time":331640,"text":"She, at over 100, taught me\nhow to make the local specialty,"},{"time":336080,"text":"which is called culurgiones,"},{"time":337760,"text":"which are these large pasta pockets"},{"time":340560,"text":"like ravioli about this size,"},{"time":343440,"text":"this size,"},{"time":344680,"text":"and they're filled\nwith high-fat ricotta and mint"},{"time":347240,"text":"and drenched in tomato sauce."},{"time":349040,"text":"And she showed me\nhow to make just the right crimp"},{"time":353000,"text":"so they wouldn't open,"},{"time":354800,"text":"and she makes them\nwith her daughters every Sunday"},{"time":357840,"text":"and distributes them\nby the dozens to neighbors and friends."},{"time":361560,"text":"And that's when I discovered\na low-fat, gluten-free diet"},{"time":364680,"text":"is not what it takes\nto live to 100 in the blue zone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367320,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":370600,"text":"Now, these centenarians' stories\nalong with the science that underpins them"},{"time":375240,"text":"prompted me to ask myself\nsome questions too,"},{"time":378080,"text":"such as, when am I going to die\nand how can I put that day off?"},{"time":382320,"text":"And as you will see,\nthe answer is not what we expect."},{"time":386840,"text":"Julianne Holt-Lunstad is a researcher\nat Brigham Young University"},{"time":390760,"text":"and she addressed this very question"},{"time":392680,"text":"in a series of studies"},{"time":394200,"text":"of tens of thousands of middle aged people"},{"time":397120,"text":"much like this audience here."},{"time":399280,"text":"And she looked at every\naspect of their lifestyle:"},{"time":402240,"text":"their diet, their exercise,"},{"time":404400,"text":"their marital status,"},{"time":405920,"text":"how often they went to the doctor,"},{"time":407600,"text":"whether they smoked or drank, etc."},{"time":410120,"text":"She recorded all of this"},{"time":412360,"text":"and then she and her colleagues\nsat tight and waited for seven years"},{"time":416960,"text":"to see who would still be breathing."},{"time":419760,"text":"And of the people left standing,"},{"time":422880,"text":"what reduced their chances\nof dying the most?"},{"time":426440,"text":"That was her question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428080,"text":"So let's now look at her data in summary,"},{"time":431640,"text":"going from the least powerful\npredictor to the strongest."},{"time":436400,"text":"OK?"},{"time":437640,"text":"So clean air, which is great,"},{"time":439920,"text":"it doesn't predict how long you will live."},{"time":443000,"text":"Whether you have your hypertension treated"},{"time":445760,"text":"is good."},{"time":447120,"text":"Still not a strong predictor."},{"time":448920,"text":"Whether you're lean or overweight,\nyou can stop feeling guilty about this,"},{"time":452440,"text":"because it's only in third place."},{"time":454840,"text":"How much exercise you get is next,"},{"time":457360,"text":"still only a moderate predictor."},{"time":459720,"text":"Whether you've had a cardiac event\nand you're in rehab and exercising,"},{"time":464480,"text":"getting higher now."},{"time":466040,"text":"Whether you've had a flu vaccine."},{"time":467680,"text":"Did anybody here know"},{"time":468960,"text":"that having a flu vaccine\nprotects you more than doing exercise?"},{"time":474720,"text":"Whether you were drinking and quit,"},{"time":477240,"text":"or whether you're a moderate drinker,"},{"time":479240,"text":"whether you don't smoke,\nor if you did, whether you quit,"},{"time":483560,"text":"and getting towards the top predictors"},{"time":487200,"text":"are two features of your social life."},{"time":490760,"text":"First, your close relationships."},{"time":493160,"text":"These are the people\nthat you can call on for a loan"},{"time":497480,"text":"if you need money suddenly,"},{"time":500120,"text":"who will call the doctor\nif you're not feeling well"},{"time":502720,"text":"or who will take you to the hospital,"},{"time":504560,"text":"or who will sit with you\nif you're having an existential crisis,"},{"time":509400,"text":"if you're in despair."},{"time":511400,"text":"Those people, that little clutch of people"},{"time":514039,"text":"are a strong predictor, if you have them,\nof how long you'll live."},{"time":517600,"text":"And then something that surprised me,"},{"time":519960,"text":"something that's called\nsocial integration."},{"time":522600,"text":"This means how much\nyou interact with people"},{"time":526680,"text":"as you move through your day."},{"time":528760,"text":"How many people do you talk to?"},{"time":530880,"text":"And these mean both\nyour weak and your strong bonds,"},{"time":534480,"text":"so not just the people\nyou're really close to,"},{"time":537000,"text":"who mean a lot to you,"},{"time":538400,"text":"but, like, do you talk to the guy\nwho every day makes you your coffee?"},{"time":542960,"text":"Do you talk to the postman?"},{"time":544760,"text":"Do you talk to the woman who walks\nby your house every day with her dog?"},{"time":548240,"text":"Do you play bridge or poker,\nhave a book club?"},{"time":551240,"text":"Those interactions\nare one of the strongest predictors"},{"time":554440,"text":"of how long you'll live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555800,"text":"Now, this leads me to the next question:"},{"time":558840,"text":"if we now spend more time online\nthan on any other activity,"},{"time":564280,"text":"including sleeping,"},{"time":565960,"text":"we're now up to 11 hours a day,"},{"time":568160,"text":"one hour more than last year, by the way,"},{"time":570680,"text":"does it make a difference?"},{"time":572520,"text":"Why distinguish\nbetween interacting in person"},{"time":576560,"text":"and interacting via social media?"},{"time":578800,"text":"Is it the same thing as being there"},{"time":581680,"text":"if you're in contact constantly\nwith your kids through text, for example?"},{"time":586200,"text":"Well, the short answer\nto the question is no,"},{"time":588360,"text":"it's not the same thing."},{"time":590040,"text":"Face-to-face contact releases\na whole cascade of neurotransmitters,"},{"time":594880,"text":"and like a vaccine,\nthey protect you now in the present"},{"time":598200,"text":"and well into the future."},{"time":600080,"text":"So simply making\neye contact with somebody,"},{"time":603600,"text":"shaking hands, giving somebody a high-five"},{"time":606200,"text":"is enough to release oxytocin,"},{"time":608280,"text":"which increases your level of trust"},{"time":610520,"text":"and it lowers your cortisol levels."},{"time":612920,"text":"So it lowers your stress."},{"time":615440,"text":"And dopamine is generated,\nwhich gives us a little high"},{"time":618280,"text":"and it kills pain."},{"time":619520,"text":"It's like a naturally produced morphine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623160,"text":"Now, all of this passes\nunder our conscious radar,"},{"time":625880,"text":"which is why we conflate\nonline activity with the real thing."},{"time":630200,"text":"But we do have evidence now,\nfresh evidence,"},{"time":632560,"text":"that there is a difference."},{"time":633920,"text":"So let's look at some of the neuroscience."},{"time":636000,"text":"Elizabeth Redcay, a neuroscientist\nat the University of Maryland,"},{"time":639320,"text":"tried to map the difference"},{"time":641160,"text":"between what goes on in our brains\nwhen we interact in person"},{"time":644840,"text":"versus when we're watching\nsomething that's static."},{"time":648080,"text":"And what she did was\nshe compared the brain function"},{"time":650533,"text":"of two groups of people,"},{"time":652600,"text":"those interacting live with her"},{"time":655920,"text":"or with one of her research associates"},{"time":658080,"text":"in a dynamic conversation,"},{"time":660280,"text":"and she compared that\nto the brain activity of people"},{"time":662800,"text":"who were watching her talk\nabout the same subject"},{"time":666560,"text":"but in a canned video, like on YouTube."},{"time":669880,"text":"And by the way, if you want to know"},{"time":671600,"text":"how she fit two people\nin an MRI scanner at the same time,"},{"time":674440,"text":"talk to me later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676360,"text":"So what's the difference?"},{"time":679280,"text":"This is your brain\non real social interaction."},{"time":682840,"text":"What you're seeing\nis the difference in brain activity"},{"time":685760,"text":"between interacting in person\nand taking in static content."},{"time":690920,"text":"In orange, you see the brain areas\nthat are associated with attention,"},{"time":695920,"text":"social intelligence --"},{"time":697160,"text":"that means anticipating\nwhat somebody else is thinking"},{"time":699760,"text":"and feeling and planning --"},{"time":701520,"text":"and emotional reward."},{"time":703080,"text":"And these areas become much more engaged"},{"time":705880,"text":"when we're interacting\nwith a live partner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710120,"text":"Now, these richer brain signatures"},{"time":712840,"text":"might be why recruiters\nfrom Fortune 500 companies"},{"time":716920,"text":"evaluating candidates"},{"time":718880,"text":"thought that the candidates were smarter"},{"time":721680,"text":"when they heard their voices"},{"time":724160,"text":"compared to when they just\nread their pitches in a text, for example,"},{"time":727440,"text":"or an email or a letter."},{"time":728880,"text":"Now, our voices and body language\nconvey a rich signal."},{"time":731680,"text":"It shows that we're thinking, feeling,"},{"time":733720,"text":"sentient human beings"},{"time":735400,"text":"who are much more than an algorithm."},{"time":737920,"text":"Now, this research by Nicholas Epley"},{"time":740000,"text":"at the University of Chicago\nBusiness School"},{"time":744440,"text":"is quite amazing because\nit tells us a simple thing."},{"time":747760,"text":"If somebody hears your voice,"},{"time":749840,"text":"they think you're smarter."},{"time":751840,"text":"I mean, that's quite a simple thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755320,"text":"Now, to return to the beginning,"},{"time":758040,"text":"why do women live longer than men?"},{"time":759960,"text":"And one major reason\nis that women are more likely"},{"time":762320,"text":"to prioritize and groom\ntheir face-to-face relationships"},{"time":765720,"text":"over their lifespans."},{"time":767400,"text":"Fresh evidence shows"},{"time":769080,"text":"that these in-person friendships"},{"time":770800,"text":"create a biological force field\nagainst disease and decline."},{"time":774800,"text":"And it's not just true of humans"},{"time":777000,"text":"but their primate relations,\nour primate relations as well."},{"time":780400,"text":"Anthropologist Joan Silk's work\nshows that female baboons"},{"time":784080,"text":"who have a core of female friends"},{"time":787000,"text":"show lower levels of stress\nvia their cortisol levels,"},{"time":790600,"text":"they live longer and they have\nmore surviving offspring."},{"time":794640,"text":"At least three stable relationships."},{"time":797040,"text":"That was the magic number."},{"time":798560,"text":"Think about it."},{"time":799800,"text":"I hope you guys have three."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802440,"text":"The power of such face-to-face contact"},{"time":806480,"text":"is really why there are\nthe lowest rates of dementia"},{"time":809320,"text":"among people who are socially engaged."},{"time":812160,"text":"It's why women who have breast cancer"},{"time":814000,"text":"are four times more likely\nto survive their disease than loners are."},{"time":819320,"text":"Why men who've had a stroke\nwho meet regularly to play poker"},{"time":823320,"text":"or to have coffee"},{"time":825000,"text":"or to play old-timer's hockey --"},{"time":827280,"text":"I'm Canadian, after all --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":828600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":829760,"text":"are better protected\nby that social contact"},{"time":832280,"text":"than they are by medication."},{"time":834320,"text":"Why men who've had a stroke\nwho meet regularly --"},{"time":837440,"text":"this is something very\npowerful they can do."},{"time":839920,"text":"This face-to-face contact\nprovides stunning benefits,"},{"time":843640,"text":"yet now almost a quarter of the population\nsays they have no one to talk to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849160,"text":"We can do something about this."},{"time":851520,"text":"Like Sardinian villagers,"},{"time":853320,"text":"it's a biological imperative\nto know we belong,"},{"time":857040,"text":"and not just the women among us."},{"time":859080,"text":"Building in-person interaction\ninto our cities, into our workplaces,"},{"time":863240,"text":"into our agendas"},{"time":865840,"text":"bolsters the immune system,"},{"time":867320,"text":"sends feel-good hormones\nsurging through the bloodstream and brain"},{"time":871360,"text":"and helps us live longer."},{"time":873840,"text":"I call this building your village,"},{"time":876520,"text":"and building it and sustaining it\nis a matter of life and death."},{"time":880760,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":888130,"text":"Helen Walters: Susan, come back.\nI have a question for you."},{"time":890920,"text":"I'm wondering if there's a middle path."},{"time":892840,"text":"So you talk about the neurotransmitters\nconnecting when in face-to-face,"},{"time":896280,"text":"but what about digital technology?"},{"time":897960,"text":"We've seen enormous improvements\nin digital technology"},{"time":900560,"text":"like FaceTime, things like that."},{"time":903040,"text":"Does that work too?"},{"time":904320,"text":"I mean, I see my nephew."},{"time":905600,"text":"He plays Minecraft\nand he's yelling at his friends."},{"time":908040,"text":"It seems like he's connecting pretty well."},{"time":910080,"text":"Is that useful? Is that helpful?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":911880,"text":"Susan Pinker: Some of the data\nare just emerging."},{"time":914240,"text":"The data are so fresh\nthat the digital revolution happened"},{"time":917240,"text":"and the health data trailed behind."},{"time":920000,"text":"So we're just learning,"},{"time":921400,"text":"but I would say\nthere are some improvements"},{"time":923440,"text":"that we could make in the technology."},{"time":925280,"text":"For example, the camera on your laptop\nis at the top of the screen,"},{"time":928760,"text":"so for example, when you're\nlooking into the screen,"},{"time":931840,"text":"you're not actually making eye contact."},{"time":933760,"text":"So something as simple\nas even just looking into the camera"},{"time":936960,"text":"can increase those neurotransmitters,"},{"time":939240,"text":"or maybe changing\nthe position of the camera."},{"time":941840,"text":"So it's not identical, but I think\nwe are getting closer with the technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":945560,"text":"HW: Great. Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":947320,"text":"SP: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":948560,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}